{
  "stem": "26728.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was assigned to the Ninth Air Force, to the 10th Fighter Group of the Ninth Air Force in England, at-- at Raydon, England.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Went through some more combat training and flew escort missions across the English Channel to France, into France, and Holland, and-- and Germany a little bit.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Escorting bombers.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then, the P-51s came in.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The P-47s were much more shorter range.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The P-51s had twice as much range as the P-47s did.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they took over the job pretty much of escorting the bombers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They could go clear to Berlin and back without any trouble.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So my unit was then assigned to air-to-ground support.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so, we were-- we did what was called targets of opportunity.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Or an assigned target from air to ground.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The ground would call us in and say we have-- we have a little-- a village, or some tanks, or some obstacle that we can't get through.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Come in and-- and tear it up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And-- and so, we would take a squadron of P-47s.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Each had two 1,000 pound bombs and 3,500 rounds of 50 caliber ammunition.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we were-- a lot of firepower.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we would, say the infantry or the-- or whoever was on the ground that was stopped, having trouble, would give us targets.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They'd use smoke and whatever.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And we would go in there, and sometimes we didn't see anything except the smoke.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We would drop our bombs, and strafe, and raise hell, tear up the territory.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And-- and they would tell us, you know, we got it or we didn't.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "If we didn't, we'd have to go back and reload and come back.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "With sometime-- that was called a sortie-- and sometimes, and some-- on some days you could-- might do four or five sorties.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
